"```sql\nSELECT \n  (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT L.ID) \n   FROM Laboratory L \n   WHERE L.PLT < 100) AS Patients_Lower_Than_Normal,\n  (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT L.ID) \n   FROM Laboratory L \n   WHERE L.PLT > 400) AS Patients_Higher_Than_Normal\nFROM Laboratory L\nWHERE L.PLT <= 100 OR L.PLT >= 400;\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the number of distinct patients with platelet levels lower than the normal range (PLT < 100) and higher than the normal range (PLT > 400) from the Laboratory table. It uses subqueries to count the distinct patient IDs for each condition."